This paper deals with information theoretic concepts such as interference alignment and mutual information optimization in the context of a multi-user downlink MIMO channel with delayed CSIT. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. However, it also involves communication systems (cs.COMM) and signal processing (cs.SI) aspects. Additionally, the paper proposes precoding methods that optimize virtual MMSE and mutual information, which are related to network information theory (cs.NI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
